These tax breaks for wealthy individuals would be paid for by the hardworking Missourians who Republicans passed a tax cut for in the last Congress, so I voted no.

Today the Democrats passed a tax break for blue state billionaires. They repealed the commonsense cap on SALT deductions, disproportionately benefitting very high-income households at the expense of working class families.

I want to know where you stand on the issues.

Take my issues survey here to let me know what's important to you. https://wagner.house.gov/issues-survey-2019 …

Today I urged my colleagues to vote YES on the USMCA trade agreement. 

The President has negotiated a deal that will strengthen our economy and benefit all Missourians, and I am glad that we can finally deliver this win to the American people. https://youtu.be/tGxhyUzH_Rk

Today I chose the Constitution over partisanship and cast my vote against the articles of impeachment. This is a crime-less impeachment and today we saw Democrats vote to undermine the results of an election without a single Republican joining them. https://wagner.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/wagner-statement-on-impeachment …

While these vital programs should never have been allowed to lapse at all, I am pleased that our continued efforts to get this legislation over the finish line worked, and I look forward to President Trump signing it into law.

 https://wagner.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/wagner-hails-senate-passage-of-debbie-smith-reauthorization-act … @RAINN @rainnaction
Alongside sexual assault survivors, I have been whipping my colleagues and Senators in a push to get this done ever since we introduced this legislation.

Now that the Debbie Smith Act is being reauthorized, our communities can better identify and prosecute violent predators and find justice for the survivors who have bravely come forward to pursue their attackers.
Survivors of sexual assault have looked to us for leadership since this critical DNA testing program was allowed to lapse in September.
I am thrilled that the Debbie Smith Reauthorization ­­Act has finally passed the Senate. #PassDSA
Thank you @RAINN for working with us to #PassDSA https://twitter.com/rainnaction/status/1207060725887381506 …

Taking your kids to work should be celebrated, not attacked.

There is nothing wrong w/ @RepMarthaRoby bringing her son to work.

I stand w/ her in the face of this disgusting attack & thank @RepKinzinger and @RepLizCheney for defending our friend who is just being a good mother. https://twitter.com/washingtonpost/status/1206823518702391296 …
